fi.tuni.tamk.tiko.tiko2a

Class HUD

  • java.lang.Object
    • fi.tuni.tamk.tiko.tiko2a.HUD
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.badlogic.gdx.Screen

    public class HUD
extends java.lang.Object
implements com.badlogic.gdx.Screen
    The HUD class for our screen, this is in use at the transition and drawing screens. It's the menu button at top left and when clicked it opens the dialog box in the middle that has continue and main menu buttons. It works by having the dialog box and its buttons being set as hidden and when the menu button at the top left is pressed, the visibility is then changed to visible. Also a boolean that indicates that the dialog box is open is then set to true. That boolean is then used at the transition screen to stop the player sprite from moving when the box is open. (To make it feel as if the game is actually paused.)
